<p>Selank is one of the few compounds that genuinely bridges the gap between anxiety relief and cognitive enhancement. Developed at Moscow's Institute of Molecular Genetics in the 1990s, it's a synthetic modification of tuftsin, a naturally occurring immune-modulating tetrapeptide.</p>

<p>What makes Selank unusual is its effect profile. Traditional anxiolytics like benzodiazepines calm you down at the cost of mental sharpness. Selank does the opposite: it reduces anxiety while improving memory, focus, and learning ability. Over 20 clinical studies back its safety and efficacy, and it's been a registered pharmaceutical in Russia since the early 2000s.</p>

<div class="d">
