<!-- ========== COMPOUND OVERVIEW ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>Selank at a Glance</h2>

<div class="cd cb">
  <div class="tg">Compound Profile</div>
  <h3>Selank (Tuftsin Analog)</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Sequence:</strong> Thr-Lys-Pro-Arg-Pro-Gly-Pro &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Type:</strong> Synthetic heptapeptide (tuftsin + PGP) &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Origin:</strong> Institute of Molecular Genetics, Moscow &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Routes:</strong> Intranasal spray (preferred), subcutaneous injection &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>FDA Status:</strong> Not approved in the US; registered anxiolytic in Russia &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Primary Actions:</strong> Anxiolytic, nootropic, immunomodulatory</p>
</div>

<p>Selank was created by attaching a Pro-Gly-Pro stabilizing tail to tuftsin (Thr-Lys-Pro-Arg), a natural peptide fragment of immunoglobulin G. This modification dramatically increases enzymatic stability and brain penetration while preserving tuftsin's immune-modulating properties.</p>

<p>For a deeper compound profile, visit <a href="https://peptidearc.com">PeptideArc</a>.</p>

